<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <title>Bonnie v<%=Bonnie::Version.current()%></title>
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", :media => "all" %>
    <%= render 'layouts/shim' %>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="landing-masthead">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <h1 class="logo">BONNIE</h1>
            <p class="tagline">A tool for testing electronic clinical quality measures</p>
          </div>
          <div class="login col-md-4">
            <a href="/users/sign_in" class="btn-login">login</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="landing-subhead">
      <div class="container">
        <a target="_blank" href="/resource/Bonnie_user_guide.pdf" class="btn btn-default">User Guide</a>
        <a target="_blank" href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/bonnie" class="btn btn-default">User Group</a>
          <a target="_blank" href="/resource/Bonnie_Integration_API_Guide_v1.pdf" class="btn btn-default">API Guide</a>
        <a target="_blank" href="http://jira.oncprojectracking.org/browse/BONNIE" class="btn btn-default">Report Bug</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <section class="highlights row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>streamlined and efficient</h2>
          <i class="fa fa-fighter-jet lg"></i>
          <p>pretesting for eCQMs</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>developer empowerment</h2>
          <i class="fa fa-bolt lg"></i>
          <p>provides specific feedback on the behavior of the CQM logic</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>meaningful use support</h2>
          <i class="fa fa-plus lg"></i>
          <p>supports the Meaningful Use (MU) Program</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section>
        <p class="lead">Bonnie is a tool for testing electronic clinical quality measures (eCQMs) designed to support streamlined and efficient pre-testing of eCQMs, particularly those used in the Meaningful Use (MU) program.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 section-heading">
          <h1 class="section-heading">Current <span class="version-num">Version 1.4</span></h1>
          <p>The version 1.4 release of Bonnie adds support for testing measures using QDM 4.2, including support for the Immunization, Diagnosis, Symptom, and Family History datatypes, as well as Encounters with Diagnoses and Laboratory Tests with a Reference Range.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h1 class="section-heading">Capabilities<span class="version-num"> v1.4</span></h1>
          <ul class="list-cap">
            <li>QDM 4.2 Support</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
    <footer>
      <div class="container">
        <p>BONNIE is sponsored by the <a href="http://cms.hhs.gov/">Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS)</a> and <a href="http://healthit.gov">Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology (ONC)</a> and has been developed by <a href="http://www.mitre.org">The MITRE Corporation</a></p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
